An international forum on democracy kicked off in Beijing with more than 500 guests from over 120 countries and regions and more than 20 international organizations participating online and offline. What have been the highlights of the forum? How has democracy developed in China? ForÂ this special episode of Dialogue, we have Dr. Wang Huiyao, counsellor of the China State Council; Helga Zepp-LaRouche, founder and president of the Schiller Institute; Michele Geraci, former under-secretary of State of the Italian Ministry of Economic Development; and Martin Sieff, senior fellow at the Global Policy Institute.